#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:293
msgid "On the other hand, if you are not satisfied with the selected data, click on :btn:`<fas fa-chevron-up>` and then on :code:`Clear collected reference data` to remove all collected data from the analysis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:297
msgid "A confirmation pop-up should prevent you from accidentally deleting everything."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:300
msgid "Existing training data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:302
msgid "Instead of collecting all of the data by hand, SEPAL provides numerous ways to include already-existing training data into your analysis. The data can be from multiple formats and will be included in the model to improve the quality of the final map."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:306
msgid "The imported files can use an extended version of the legend provided in the previous step, but to avoid unexpected behaviour, at least one of the classes of your legend and the provided training data need to match."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:310
msgid "If the added training data are outside of the image to classify, they will have no impact on the final result (with the exception of the \"SEPAL recipe\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:312
msgid "To add new data, click :btn:`<fas fa-plus> Add` and choose the type of data to import:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:319
msgid "CSV"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:321
msgid "By selecting :btn:`csv file`, SEPAL will request a file from your computer in :code:`.csv` format. The file needs to include two pieces of information: geographic coordinates and class value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/cookbook/classification.rst:323
msgid "This can be done using coordinates in :code:`EPSG:4326` latitude and longitude, as well as a `GeoJSON <https://geojson.org>`__ compatible point object. The file can embed other multiple columns that will not be considered during the analysis."
